      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why E-Ending Words Matter in Scrabble</h2>
      <p>With 12 E tiles in the bag, you'll almost always have at least one on your rack. The silent E pattern is the most productive word-ending in English — it transforms short consonant-heavy stems into valid plays (HOP → HOPE, GAM → GAME, TUB → TUBE). This makes E the ultimate hooking letter for extending words already on the board.</p>
      <p>The highest-scoring E-enders pair the common ending with Z (10 pts) and Q (10 pts). Words like SQUEEZE (25 points), FREEZE (18 points), and BLAZE (16 points) show how a humble silent E can anchor genuinely powerful plays. Because E-ending words are so numerous, you can almost always find one that hits a premium square, making E one of the most tactically flexible letters in your rack.</p>

